    <bioghist encodinganalog="5451">
      <p> The Butte Machinist Union, International
		  Association of Machinists, Lodge 88, was organized in Butte, Montana, in 1891.
		  Officers included Master Machinist August Heimbach, Foreman Charles O'Rourke,
		  Recording Secretary James Hamlin, and Treasurer Thomas Ogle. </p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="5202">
      <head>Content Description:</head>
      <p> Records. 1915-1972. 2 linear feet. The
		  records of the International Association of Machinists, Lodge 88, of Butte,
		  Montana, contain general correspondence (1943-1953, 1967, 1969); financial
		  records (1937-1970), including memberhip information; legal documents
		  (1937-1960), consisting of labor agreements with a variety of employers;
		  minutes (1915-1921; 1943-1959); reports (1947); subject files (1966-1967)
		  pertaining to The Anaconda Company; and miscellany. Artifacts have been
		  transferred to the Museum. </p>
    </scopecontent>
